                <summary>Detailed description of renovation of County courthouse interior, including
                    layout and furinishings. Sully portrait of Chief Justice John Marshall hangs
                    above the Bench. Committe in Charge=Col. Baldwin; J.D. Imboden; Benj. Crawford;
                    John Churchamn; Wm. A. Bell; Architecht=Mr. Starkeweather, of Baltimore;
                    Contractor=Harman J. Lushbaugh; Woodworking=William Lushbaugh; Mr. Kice;
                    Plastering=Samuel J. Lushbaugh; Painting &amp; graining=Wm. L. Balthis;
                    Marblework=Mr. Marquis; Mr. Kelly</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Things That Need Mending</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Controversy among citizens over the Town Clock. It needs mending. Also
                    calls for the construction of a "suitable" water works for the town. Streets
                    need to be fixed; cemetary grounds should be improved &amp; beautified.
                    Notes that since writing, work has begun on piping water to the town's main
                    spring; also the clock has been restarted.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>The Insurrection Rumors</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Rumors of insurrection from around the counry proved groundless. Inspired
                    by slaves expressing interest in Fremont. Complins about mob spirit driving
                    these fears, but also cautions about maintianing firm discipline.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Negro Hiring</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Prices for hiring slaves from around the state; compared with Stuanton.
                    Local prices: farmhand=$120; 17-18yr old boy=$80; women=$60-75;
                girls=$30-45</summary>
            </div>
